    AboutAbout

    From being a kid , who spent most of her time in the playground than in the classroom to leading a team of software professionals in SD for Analytics Platform - that is how I would summarize myself.

    I am a National level throw ball player, who secured admission in one of the esteemed colleges of the state through Sports quota. Graduated as a Civil Engineer, but looking at my Headline, it is evident that life had different plans for me. Started off my career as a Production support engineer for a global web application under Analytics platform in Retail domain.
    Being a quick learner, started handling service delivery, CI&CD and system management for the application.
    I have an etch to explore different roles and took up the opportunity of being the Business Analyst of the same Project after 2 years . I learnt a great deal about requirement analysis and stake holder management in that period and when time came to step up(after a year) , I took up the role of leading the Service delivery team.

    From pursuing to play a team sport , I understood one thing about myself - I Love to win , but helping the team to win brings great satisfaction and joy to self. My experience of being a captain of a state team has played a major role in sculpting myself into an efficient leader.

    Looking forward for more learnings and interesting opportunities!
